By using Hacker Clean, you consent to the data practices described in this policy.

1. Information We Collect
Hacker Clean may collect the following types of information while providing its services:

User Data: We may collect user IDs, usernames, and other publicly available information on Discord to perform moderation and scanning tasks.

Server Data: When used in a server, Hacker Clean may access server details such as server ID, member lists, and roles to provide relevant moderation and security functionalities.

Interaction Data: We may collect information about how users interact with the bot, including commands sent and actions performed.

2. How We Use the Information
We use the information we collect to:

Provide moderation services, such as scanning for and identifying users with matching IDs.

Respond to user commands and requests.

Improve the functionality and reliability of Hacker Clean.

Ensure compliance with Discord's Community Guidelines and Terms of Service.

3. Data Storage
All data collected by Hacker Clean is stored temporarily and securely. We do not retain personal data for longer than necessary for the operation of the bot's services.

Hacker Clean does not store sensitive personal data such as private messages, email addresses, or other identifiable information beyond the scope necessary for the bot's functionality.

4. Data Sharing
We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties except when required by law or when necessary for providing the services of the bot.

Hacker Clean will only share data with third-party services or entities if required for:

Performing specific tasks related to bot operation (e.g., data storage services).

Complying with legal obligations or requests from law enforcement.

5. Permissions and Data Access
By inviting Hacker Clean to your server, server administrators grant the bot specific permissions to read messages and interact with users within the server. These permissions may include:

Reading messages in text channels.

Sending messages to channels.

Managing roles or kicking/banning users (if applicable).

6. Bot Data Processing
The data collected is used only for providing the core functionalities of Hacker Clean, such as:

Scanning and identifying users in a server based on their user ID.

Responding to server-specific requests, such as banning, kicking, or leaving users as-is.

7. Third-Party Services
Hacker Clean may use third-party services or APIs to provide specific features. These services are governed by their own privacy policies. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party services we use.

8. Security
We take reasonable steps to ensure that your data is protected against unauthorized access, alteration, or destruction. However, please be aware that no method of data transmission or storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of any data collected.

9. User Control
You can manage the information that is shared with Hacker Clean by:

Removing the bot from your server at any time, which will stop the bot from accessing your server's data.

Reaching out to us if you have any concerns about the data we collect or how it's used.

10. Data Retention
We retain user and server data only as long as necessary for the operation of the bot. Once the data is no longer needed, it will be deleted. We do not store personal data beyond the duration required for the features of the bot to function.

11. Children's Privacy
Hacker Clean does not knowingly collect or solicit information from anyone under the age of 13. If we learn that we have inadvertently collected data from a child under the age of 13, we will delete such information as soon as possible.

12. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. Any changes will be posted here with the updated date.
